Git (on Mac OSX)
-------

* Install git, prepend /usr/local/git/bin to /etc/paths
  * git config --global user.name Kimo Rosenbaum
  * git config --global user.email
* Disk Utility -> New Image (for GitHub)
  * Format: Mac OS Extended (Case-sensitive, Journaled)
  * Image Format: sparse bundle disk image
* Add GitHub Volume to startup items (hidden)
* mkdir ~/work
* ln -s /Volumes/GitHub ~/work/github.com
* Create ssh key for github:
  * install -d -m 0700 ~/.ssh
  * ssh-keygen -t rsa -f ~/.ssh/github
  * Add key to github
  * ~/.ssh/config:
Host github.com
  User git
  IdentitiesOnly yes
  IdentityFile ~/.ssh/github

/usr/local/bin/merge_pr
#!/bin/sh
set -e

if [ -z "${2}" ]; then
	echo "Usage: ${0##*/} pr branch" >&2
	exit 1
fi

pr="${1}"
branch="${2}"

git checkout main
git pull origin

git fetch origin "${branch}"

git merge --no-ff -m "Merge pull request #${pr} from ${branch}" "origin/${branch}"
git push -u origin main

git push origin --delete "${branch}"

if git show-ref --quiet "refs/heads/${branch}"; then
	git branch -d "${branch}"
fi
